      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Under Uniform Hospital Discharge Data Set (UHDDS) guidelines used by U.S. hospitals and insurers, inpatient diagnoses are coded as follows: Possible indications and cardiovascular risk factors were assessed using diagnoses and procedures recorded in administrative data during the 183 days before the patient's IGIV treatment date."
